The paper deals with the distributed computation of a maximum matching in a network graph, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The algorithm presented in the paper involves communication and message passing between nodes, which is a common theme in distributed systems (cs.DS). The problem of finding a maximum matching is a classic problem in graph theory (cs.DM). The CONGEST model, which is used in the paper, is a well-known model for studying distributed algorithms in computer networks (cs.NI). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of randomized algorithms, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.GT).
